The U.S. Supreme Court declines to hear a petition (Eaton Corp v. Z F Meritor) from Eaton Corp., letting stand a U.S. 3rd Circuit Court ruling on an antitrust issue that may limit the use of loyalty discounts in the form of rebates as a way of locking in customers. (Reuters)Macy's loses a bid to stop JC Penney from selling unbranded housewares designed by Martha Stewart. (The New York Times)